article.headline: Brown 53, Dartmouth 33
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Damon Huffman scored 14 points to help Brown beat Dartmouth 53-33 on Saturday night. Dartmouth (8-15, 3-7 Ivy League) led 16-11 when Brown (9-16, 4-6) closed out the first half with a 13-0 run for a 24-16 lead. Mark McAndrew had 13 points and 11 rebounds for Brown. DeVon Mosley (10 points) was the only Dartmouth player to reach double figures as the Big Green shot just 26 percent from the floor. Dartmouth also was 0-for-12 from the 3-point line. Brown put together an 11-0 run to take a 47-28 lead with 5:10 to play.
